main event: A possible UFO sighting was reported on August 22, 1955 in Cutlerville, Michigan.
interesting points: The object was described as 10 jet-shaped objects that were green, white, and climbed from an estimated 3,000 feet to 20,000 feet.
Three F-86D aircraft were scrambled to intercept the object, but no airborne sighting was made.
The object was initially evaluated as a 'very bright star' by the Operations Officer.
Two photographs were reportedly taken of the object, but they were not included in the report.
The report describes the object as having a 'greenish, red, and white' color, and a 'light with no definite outline' shape.
sighted object: 10 jet-shaped objects, greenish-red-white color, light with no definite outline
